The paper discusses a system that integrates programmatic and direct manipulation interfaces for the domain of Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HCI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions heuristics for dealing with ambiguities, which suggests that it may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses a novel workflow that can augment traditional programming systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Development (cs.SD) sub-category.
